data.sail_code:
/*

DESCRIPTION: This rule represents the scheduling configuration of the due and overdue email process.
Modify this rule to change the frequency or time at which the process runs.

DEFAULT BEHAVIOR: The due and overdue email process is scheduled to run every weekday at 4:00 AM EST.

CUSTOMIZATION STEPS: Configure a new due and overdue email schedule by changing the map configuration below.
See inline comments about what each field of the map represents.


EXPECTED OUTPUT TYPE: Map, with fields `daysOfWeek`, `daysOfMonth`, `timeInEst`, `isDisabled`

*/
a!map(
  /*A list of days of the week which to run this sync process.*/
  /*Valid values: SUNDAY, MONDAY, TUESDAY, WEDNESDAY, THURSDAY, FRIDAY, SATURDAY*/
  daysOfWeek: {"MONDAY", "TUESDAY", "WEDNESDAY", "THURSDAY", "FRIDAY"},

  /*A list of days of the month which to run this sync process.*/
  /*Valid values: Any numbers between 1 and 31*/
  daysOfMonth: {},

  /*Note, generally you'd only configure daysOfWeek OR daysOfMonth, not both. If
  you specify both, then the process will run when either daysOfWeek and daysOfMonth
  are true.*/

  /*The 24-hour time in Eastern Standard Time when to run this process.*/
  /*Generally this would be set during off-hours.*/
  timeInEst: time(4, 0, 0),

  /*If the following is set to true, the due and overdue email process won't run at all.*/
  isDisabled: false
)

